</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1">The union actively engages with government bodies, contributing to policy-making and representing members’ interests.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1">The NEU offers a range of training and development opportunities to enhance the skills and knowledge of its members.

</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-28_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-29_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-30_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-32_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-33_ pf-text-1"><strong>National Education Union (NEU)</strong> - The NEU is a professional association and trade union for educators in the United Kingdom. It was formed from the amalgamation of the National Union of Teachers (NUT) and the Association of Teachers and Lecturers (ATL) in 2017.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>ComplyPlus™ </strong>- Is a comprehensive legislation and regulatory compliance management software designed to help organisations in the education sector meet statutory and regulatory requirements efficiently.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-37_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-38_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h3">The importance of the NEU in education
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-41_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-42_ pf-text-1"><strong>Advocacy and representation</strong> - The NEU is instrumental in advocating for the rights and welfare of educational professionals. By engaging in dialogue with government entities and influencing policy decisions, the NEU ensures that educators' voices are heard and their needs are met. This advocacy is crucial in shaping a supportive working environment that directly impacts the quality of education delivered to students.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-44_ pf-text-1"><strong>Professional development </strong>- Continuous professional development (CPD) is vital for maintaining high educational standards. The NEU provides various CPD opportunities, helping educators stay updated with the latest teaching methodologies, technological advancements, and regulatory changes. This commitment to professional growth ensures that educators can consistently deliver high-quality education.










</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-46_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-47_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-48_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation and regulations
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-50_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-51_ pf-text-1"><strong>Education Act 2002</strong> - The Education Act 2002 lays down the legal framework for the operation of schools and educational institutions in the UK. It covers areas such as curriculum delivery, staff employment, and student welfare. The NEU works within this framework to uphold educators' rights and responsibilities.








</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-53_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and Safety at Work Act 1974</strong> - Outlines employers' responsibilities to ensure the health and safety of their employees. In the educational context, this includes ensuring safe working conditions for teachers and support staff. The NEU guides and supports its members in adhering to these regulations, promoting a safe and conducive working environment.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-55_ pf-text-1"><strong>Equality Act 2010</strong> - The Equality Act 2010 prohibits discrimination in the workplace and educational settings. The NEU advocates for inclusive practices and policies that promote equality and diversity in education. This includes fighting against discrimination based on race, gender, disability, and other protected characteristics.










</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-57_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-58_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-59_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices for implementation
